narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments:
As a result of this course, I have become a more liberated writer. Learning more about grammar, metaphors, "tightening and trimming the fat", etc. made my writing pieces more interesting to read, both in my opinion and based on others' feedback. I believe the skills I've gained will help me craft more elegant essays, during my college application, when I'll write essays as a student, and at any other point in the future.
I also really enjoyed extracting information and the outline from a passage written by someone else. I believe this is an essential skill to have, so I am very grateful to have honed it from this course.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments:
The course covers all the necessary aspects of reading and writing, and the instructor makes sure everyone becomes an expert on every step of each of those skills.
Of course, it was always fun to free-write every class and then make a Haiku on our very last one!

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes. I especially feel the writing part will help tons of students as writing engaging essays without suffering from frustration out of writer's block is a skill that not many people have because of the rather faulty way in which writing is normally taught.
